44 (i) An ammunition magazine that attaches to the pistol outside of the pistol grip;
45 (ii) A threaded barrel that can accommodate a barrel extender, flash suppressor,
46 forward handgrip, or silencer;
47 (iii) A shroud that is attached to, or partially or completely encircles, the barrel and
48 that allows the shooter to hold the firearm with the nontrigger hand without being
49 burned;
50 (iv) A manufactured weight of 50 ounces or more when the pistol is unloaded; or
51 (v) A semiautomatic version of an automatic firearm; or
52 (E) A semiautomatic shotgun that has at least two of the following:
53 (i) A folding or telescoping stock;
54 (ii) A pistol grip that protrudes conspicuously beneath the action of the weapon;
55 (iii) A fixed magazine capacity in excess of five rounds; or
56 (iv) The capability to accommodate a detachable magazine."
57 SECTION 2.
58 Said part is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
59 "16-11-172.1.
60 (a) No transfer or purchase of a semiautomatic assault weapon conducted by a licensed
61 importer, licensed manufacturer, or licensed dealer shall be completed until the tenth day
62 after the initiation of such transfer or purchase; provided, however, that the calculation of
63 the ten days shall not include Saturdays, Sundays, or state or federal holidays; and
64 provided, further, that an NICS check may be conducted within such ten days.
65 (b) Licensed importers, licensed manufacturers, and licensed dealers shall, during normal
66 business hours, make records available for inspection by any law enforcement agency for
67 purposes of any criminal investigation.
68 (c) Subsection (a) of this Code section shall not apply when a semiautomatic assault
69 weapon is being transferred to or purchased by:
